Using .fz.toml for redis/src. You need add fz.toml in redis/src dir.

Example:
# ForgeZero configuration for Redis server build
output = "redis-server"

include = [
    "deps/libc/include",
    "deps/lua/src",
    "deps/hiredis",
    "deps/jemalloc/include"
]

libs = ["m"]


Also add fz.toml in redis/deps/hiredis for compiling dependencies. Example:

name = "hiredis"
source_files = [
  "hiredis.c",
  "net.c", 
  "read.c",
  "sds.c",
  "sockcompat.c",
  "ssl.c",
  "async.c",
  "alloc.c",
  "dict.c"
]

[dep_build]
enabled = true
skip_tests = true

NEXT STEP:

using ForgeZero :)

fz -dir redis/src -out redis-server -mode c

For check time:

time fz -dir redis/src -out redis-server -mode c

optional with performance options:

fz -p performance -dir redis/src -out redis-server -mode -c -j $(nproc) 

If you want using your toolchain(like gcc, clang, zig) then write so:

fz -dir redis/src -out redis-server -toolchain clang -mode -c 

